ions</a> to buy Bethesda was to stop <em>Starfield</em> from becoming exclusive to PlayStation like <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/ghostwire-tokyo"><em>Ghostwire: Tokyo</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/deathloop"><em>Deathloop</em></a> .</p><p> “I&#39;m aware that it&#39;s easy to just select the exit button, however this just feels gross,” <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/xbox/comments/17m90hk/advertisement_after_turning_on_the_console/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complained</a> one player.</p><blockquote class="reddit-embed-bq" style="height:500px" ><p> <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/xbox/comments/17m90hk/advertisement_after_turning_on_the_console/">Advertisement after turning on the console</a><br /> by <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/ThatCatPerson9564/">u/ThatCatPerson9564</a> in <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/xbox/">xbox</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://embed.reddit.com/widgets.js" charset="UTF-8"></script></p><p> “It&#39;s not as if it needs the extra marketing, anyone who wants it will buy it regardless. It&#39;s not like they&#39;ve never heard of it before seeing this splash screen on boot up,” <a href="https://twitter.com/Juan915_/status/1720383959714910474">added</a> another.</p><p> Others <a href="https://twitter.com/supstarf/status/1720146353211187299">pointed</a> out that there is no impetus to purchase <em>Call Of Duty: Modern Warfare 3</em> and so it isn&#39;t that intrusive, but some were <a href="https://twitter.com/JezCorden/status/1720146782791864595">worried</a> that it could set a precedent for future advertisements.</p><p> In other gaming news, Konami seemingly suggested that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/silent-hill-remakes-revealed-in-konamis-third-quarter-results-3529142">there is more than one <em>Silent Hill</em> remake</a> as well as Bloober Team&#39;s <em>Silent Hill 2</em> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/call-of-duty-mode